<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Lynet on 02-19-2002 05:18 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">You have more than enough folks for this.

You can get the sceptre, or you can also hand the dwarf i
n Thurg a bottle of Karsin acid.  Well, actually you pour it into his glass and he drops the needed gem as he dashes outside to lose his lunch.  The karsin acid drops from the orcs in the front part of Crystal Caverns, and is no drop.

Folks already explained how to get the wolf harness.  Again, a ranger with snare and panic animal should be able to solo this part.  If you hang out to heal and buff it will go faster.

For the final fight, remember the following sequence:
turn in harness to broodmom
two giants walk out of the fort
Brood mom walks up to the fort
fergul despawns and respawns after broodmom gets there
Broodmom kills the other giant, Fergul runs to the zone
you kill fergul and loot pants from him.  Anyone can loot the pants, although they are nodrop.
Broodmom walks back to the cave entrance and then despawns.

Do not aggro Fergul and the other giant until after broodmom shows up and they despawn/respawn.  I suspect that many of the bugs may have been related to folks aggroing Fergul too early.

I killed Fergul with cleric 35, warrior 54, druid 53.  We got him easily and also took care of a frost giant elite who got too close to us, although the elite was a mite nervous-making.

It is highly likely that one or two giants will join the fight regardless of where you choose to engage Fergul.  I have always fought him on the other corner of the fort - if he walks out and stands front right we kill him outside the front left.  Giants always show up at the most inconvenient time, I can see why Tunare is cranky with them.

And finally, broodmom is currently bugged and has been replaced with a placeholder. 

They are good pants, and I love my Velious leather look.  It makes me look so innocent and harmless.  Of course the Luclin leather look is not so innocent and not so harmless, and that is also fun.  <grin>

Lynet Beaumains, The Damosel Savage</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
